The paper addresses the problem of rule-based stream data cleaning, which involves managing and processing large amounts of data in real-time. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to data management, data streams, and distributed systems. Specifically, cs.DB (databases), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing), cs.DM (data mining), and cs.SI (social and information networks) are all potential categories that could be relevant to this paper.
